AUDIO: 'Welcome to this step-by-step guide on how to use Animate in Mago. Animate is specifically designed to transform and replace characters in your videos without affecting the background. After importing our video and trimming the interesting part of our video, we can'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'start by selecting the animate model at the top of the settings tab. You can either import an image of your character or use our image to image model to create your stylized reference. We have many models. Let\'s use seedream. You can'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'import a reference image and write your prompt. Don\'t hesitate to optimize it to test several results. Click use this when ready. In the basic settings, you have your stylized frame and also the'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt field. Use our automatic prompt or simply describe your scene. With Animate, you can focus your prompt on the character you transform. Now, head to the advanced settings. Select the'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quality up to 1,280 for now. for this model. Enable interpolation if you want faster renders. You can then play with pose and face strengths to choose how tightly the animation should follow the'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
